resources.description:
Tooling method to check if the API is deployed without any problems.
Internally checks also for DB connection and the DB state (migrations).

Result:
```json
{
  "code": 200,
  "status": {
    "database": "OK",
    "migrations": "OK"
  }
}
```

Should return an error response.

```json
{
  "errors": [
    {
      "id": "aba11e82-5e8d-455f-aeb2-768550479454",
      "title": "StandardError",
      "detail": "Bad request",
      "status": "bad_request"
    }
  ]
}
```

Return the battery level for a given drone.

Typical expected response:

```json
{
	"type": "Drone",
	"id": 2,
	"battery_level": 80
}
```

If an invalid drone is specified the response is 404 Not found. Sample:

```json
{
  "errors": [
    {
      "id": "489c014c-1595-4df2-aeab-b510b14bc890",
      "title": "ActiveRecord::RecordNotFound",
      "detail": "Couldn't find Drone with 'id'=23",
      "status": "not_found"
    }
  ]
}
```
